<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - MANIFOLDS AND EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION (EGR) - Installation -
        Exhaust Manifolds and Tubing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26503.4.3" graphiccount="8">
        <title>Exhaust Manifolds and Tubing</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s26503.4.3.1">
            <title>Right Exhaust Manifold</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing exhaust manifolds, only use prevailing torque hex flange bolts having an
                        interference thread.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650340" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd14/D1402A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Right exhaust manifold bolt and spacer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Anti-seize compound</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply anti-seize compound to all bolt threads.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650341" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd14/D1424.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Torque sequence for exhaust manifold mounting bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right exhaust manifold</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left exhaust manifold</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position exhaust manifold gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install right exhaust manifold, using eight M8 x 40 prevailing torque hex flange bolts
                    and spacers. Start with the second bolt from the rear on top. The hole diameter is smaller, to allow
                    alignment of the remaining bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts to the special torque and in the specified sequence .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650342" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1517.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Mounting bolts for right exhaust tube</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply anti-seize compound to two M8 x 60 bolts securing the right exhaust tube assembly
                    to the exhaust manifold flange with two prevailing torque nuts. Loosely assembly bolts and nuts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650343" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd14/D1441.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>EGR cooler V-clamp</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install steel gasket for EGR cooler.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach right exhaust tube assembly to EGR cooler assembly with V-clamp. Do not tighten
                    V-clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s26503.4.3.2">
            <title>Left Exhaust Manifold</title>
            <figure id="f2650344" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd14/D1428.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Bolt and spacer for left exhaust manifold</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Anti-seize compound</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply anti-seize compound to all bolt threads.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position exhaust manifold gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install left exhaust manifold, using eight M8 x 40 prevailing torque hex flange bolts
                    and spacers. Start with the second bolt from the rear on top. The hole diameter is smaller, to allow
                    alignment of the remaining bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts to specified torque and in the specified sequence .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650345" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd17/D1704.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>EBP sensor tube fitting</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply anti-seize compound to the threads of the EBP sensor tube fitting.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install EBP sensor tube to exhaust manifold and tighten fitting to the special torque
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650346" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1558.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Exhaust tube bolts (upper right)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply anti-seize compound to the threads of two M8 x 30 bolts and prevailing torque
                    nuts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new exhaust tube gasket and secure the shielded tube exhaust assembly (upper
                    right side) to the right exhaust tube assembly. Loosely assemble bolts and nuts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650347" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1504.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Mounting bolts for shielded tube exhaust assembly on left exhaust manifold</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply anti-seize compound to two M8 x 60 bolts securing the shielded tube exhaust
                    assembly to the exhaust manifold flange. Loosely assemble bolts and nuts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For VGT installation procedure, see .</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After VGT installation, torque all bolts for VGT tubing in the following order:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Shielded exhaust tube assembly at right exhaust tube (upper flange)</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Turbocharger exhaust adapter V-clamp</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">EGR cooler V-clamp</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Shielded exhaust tube assembly at left manifold</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Exhaust tube assembly at right manifold</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <para>See for special torque specifications.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
